\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972 
 idempotency. This ensures that after the first successful build, if the script is run, the system state will again remain the same, and there won't be any errors or duplicates just because the script is run more than once.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972 DSC checks the current system st
ate before applying changes, ensuring only missing or incorrect configurations are fixed. This is critical for reliable rebuilds and supports the requirement for repeatable automation.
\par The configuration logic for the BarmBuzz system is divided into nine cl
early defined chronological layers. Layer 0 prepares evidence directories, while Layer 1 installs required Windows features. Layer 2 handles domain promotion and uses WaitForADDomain to make sure that Active Directory is fully available before continuing.
 }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972 This wait for Active Directory availability is more important as other layers depend on this}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972  such}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972  as OU creation (Layer 3), group creation (Layer 4), and user provisioning (Layer 5)}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972 , which}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972  rely on a healthy domain. Layers 6 to 8 configure RBAC, GPOs, and FGPP, respectively}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid866733\charrsid3422972 .}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972  Layer 9 automatically collects evidence outputs. This layered design ensures correct execution order and simplifies troubleshooting.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
