\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972 During the execution of the script, the server is to be rebooted after the initial steps are carried out. This is approached using Local Configuration Manager (LCM) with attribut
e ActionAfterReboot = ContinueConfiguration and RebootNodeIfNeeded = $true. These configuration}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid592992\charrsid3422972 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972  and settings }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid592992\charrsid3422972 allow}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7485840\charrsid3422972  the system to continue the execution of the script after rebooting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6096347\charrsid3422972 Security hygiene requires that passwords not be stored in plaintext in t
he codebase. This security measure is handled by administrative credentials by injecting PSCredential objects at runtime through the Run_BuildMain.ps1 script. Credentials such as DomainAdminCredential and DsrmCredential are passed securely as parameters, 
ensuring sensitive data is never exposed in source-controlled files.
\par Finally, DSC produces compiled .mof files, which act as inspectable artefacts of the final configuration. These support validation, auditing, and troubleshooting, strengthening the overall reliability of the solution.
\par {\*\bkmkstart _Toc225173795}{\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s1 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf19\dbch\af31501\insrsid16138336\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 4)\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\qj \fi-360\li360\ri0\sl360\slmult1
\keep\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls1\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf19\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31501\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid16138336\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 Repository Structure{\*\bkmkend _Toc225173795}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31507\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972 The }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 GitHub}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972  repository provided by }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972 tutor contains all the necessary files for this system}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972  but students are advised not }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972 change the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 structure}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972  of the folders and are only }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 to }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972 modify two files 1. StudentConfig.ps1 and AllNodes.psd1.  All scripts reference files relative to the root directory, ensuring consistency between environments.
\par Run_BuildMain.ps1 is the main orchestrator for system building, and it acts as the main entry point. It controls th
e entire build process because it loads all the configuration data, compiles DSC, and applies the configurations to the target node. By having a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5833606\charrsid3422972 single-entry}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972  point, the execution process is simple, repeatable, and easy to follow during both automated testing and the live build.
\par All of the environmental data, such as IP addresses, domain names, and node-specific settings, is separated from the logic and stored in DSC\\Data\\AllNodes.psd1. This separation improves maintainability because changes to the environm
ent do not require editing the core configuration code. This centralized approach works best because it provides maximum scalability, as more nodes can be easily added to AllNode.ps1 file and no other file is to be modified.
\par The actual logic for building the AD objects and GPOs is contained within DSC\\Configurations\\
StudentConfig.ps1. This file defines the full Desired State Configuration, including domain setup, OU creation, group and user provisioning, RBAC configuration, and policy deployment. Keeping lo
gic separate from data follows best practice and improves readability and debugging.
\par There is also a folder for evidence where all the logs and screenshots are to be placed. There is a folder for }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid866733\charrsid3422972 all the evidence}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7240499\charrsid3422972 , for example, Evidence/AD, Evidence/AI_LOG, Evidence/DSC, Evidence/GPOBackups, Evidence/Gitreflog, Evidence/HealthCheck, Evidence/Pester, and Evidence/screenshots.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid866733\charrsid3422972 
