The git clone command will create a new folder named BarmBuzz with all the directories and code inside that folder in the C drive. The user can access all the files and documentation from there. 
\par {\*\bkmkstart _Toc225173798}{\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s2 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\cf19\dbch\af31501\insrsid5440959\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 b)\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qj \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb40\sl360\slmult1
\keep\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls1\ilvl1\outlinelevel1\adjustright\rin0\lin720\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs28\cf19\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31501\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5440959\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 Step-by-Step Sequence{\*\bkmkend _Toc225173798}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31507\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5440959\charrsid3422972 Run_BuildMain.ps1 is the main entry po
int in the script. It then loads all the libraries, calls other files and functions to orchestrate the whole automation. This procedure is divided into five phases for maintainability. Phase 1 configures the Local Configuration Manager (LCM) and network. 
Phase 2 compiles the MOF and outputs that file in the Evidence/Output folder. This file is compiled via Windows PowerShell 5.1, and then this file is applied. Then, in the next phase, Active Directory Domain Service installation starts. 
\par After a successful build system undergoes an automatic reboot for DC promotion. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10583308\charrsid3422972 
The server reboots automatically, but for LCM, the automatic reboot ActionAfterReboot = ContinueConfiguration setting is applied in the script to reduce the manual workload and enable automatic e
xecution of the script even after a necessary system reboot. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5440959\charrsid3422972 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10583308\charrsid3422972 In the third step, there is a wait for LCM to complete its job. Its status is checked via the command Get-DscConfigurationStatus | Select-Object Status.
\par Next verification is done to check for any errors or failures in the automation. To achieve this goal PowerShell commands used are Get-ADDomain, Get-ADOrganizationalUnit, Get-ADUser, Get-ADGroup, Get-GPO, and Get-ADFineGrainedPasswordPolicy.
\par Lastly, Pester Tests validate the system. These tests are to run using commands .\\Tests\\Pester\\Invoke-Validation.ps1. It is expected to pass 109+ tests. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14038560\charrsid3422972 
\par {\*\bkmkstart _Toc225173799}{\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s1 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs32\cf19\dbch\af31501\insrsid10583308\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 6)\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s1\ql \fi-360\li360\ri0\sl360\slmult1
\keep\keepn\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\ls1\outlinelevel0\adjustright\rin0\lin360\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31503\afs24\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 
\b\fs32\cf19\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31501\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af31503 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10583308\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 Idempotence and Re-run behavior}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af31503 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10583308\charrsid8393392 {\*\bkmkend _Toc225173799}
\par {\*\bkmkstart _Toc225173800}{\listtext\pard\plain\ltrpar \s2 \rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\fs28\cf19\dbch\af31501\insrsid11288052\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 a)\tab}}\pard\plain \ltrpar\s2\qj \fi-360\li720\ri0\sb40\sl360\slmult1
