\b\fs28\cf19\lang1033\langfe1033\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af31501\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11288052\charrsid3422972 \hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 R\hich\af0\dbch\af31501\loch\f0 e-Run Expectations
{\*\bkmkend _Toc225173800}
\par }\pard\plain \ltrpar\qj \li0\ri0\sl360\slmult1\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid8393392 \rtlch\fcs1 \af31507\afs22\alang1025 \ltrch\fcs0 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid797375\charrsid3422972 Running Run_BuildMain.ps1 yields no new configuration or files. This behavior is called idempotence, wh
ere executing the scripts a second time, given no changes are made to the script, finishes the execution quickly without any duplicate files or errors. In the case of BarmBuzz, the second time build completes under one minute. This indicates that the syst
em is already in the desired state. This gives significant proof that the build process is repeatable and safe to rerun}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3422972\charrsid3422972  }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
