\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid797375\charrsid3422972 This type of behavior works because Local Configuration Manager checks the current state of the system with the desired state, and if both }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8393392\charrsid3422972 matches}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid797375\charrsid3422972 , it completely skips the actions. This approach prevents the duplication of organ
izational data like users, organizational units (OUs), or policies. The biggest advantage of this approach is the protection against configuration drift. Also, there is consistency across the multiple executions, and there is no need for manual verificati
on. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1592869\charrsid3422972 To ensure that the DSC does not create any users before the organizational units exist, the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8393392\charrsid3422972 Depends On}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1592869\charrsid3422972  property is used with each such field. This property enforces the strict execution order}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5603125\charrsid3422972 . }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid15482295\charrsid3422972 
For example, before any object of Active Directory is created, it is mandatory for WaitForADDomain to complete. In the same way, parent OUs are to be created before child OUs, and groups are to be created before group members are assigned. FGPP configurat
ion also depends on the existence of the admin groups. Thus, the DependsOn property helps enforce these constraints of dependency among different components, helps avoid critical failures, and ensures reliable orchestration}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14038560\charrsid3422972  }{\field\flddirty{\*\fldinst {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14038560\charrsid3422972  ADDIN ZOTERO_ITEM CSL_CITATION \{"citationID":"4dm0R4oi","properties":\{
"formattedCitation":"(Chaganti, 2018)","plainCitation":"(Chaganti, 2018)","noteIndex":0\},"citationItems":[\{"id":32,"uris":["http://zotero.org/users/local/wkjr8q4f/items/H769W3VY"],"itemData":\{"id":32,"type":"book","abs
tract":"Use Windows PowerShell Desired State Configuration (DSC) to configure your infrastructure on-premises and in the cloud. In an environment where changes and deployments are happening all the time, DSC makes the necessary adjustments to the system s
o
 you don't have to. Pro PowerShell Desired State Configuration shows you how. PowerShell Desired State Configuration (DSC) is a powerful configuration management platform that makes it easier than ever to perform configuration management of your infrastru
c
ture, whether on-premises or in the cloud. With Pro PowerShell Desired State Configuration , Ravikanth Chaganti revises and significantly expands his previous edition, bringing you a complete in-depth reference for applying this evolving technology in you
r
 day-to-day work. What's new in this edition? Get up-to-date, in-depth guidance on DSC in the data center Understand the central role that DSC plays in DevOps today Integrate DSC into build and release management tools Learn to think and act like a develo
p
er when automating your configuration management, creating a testable, robust process that you can use again and again Find out why and how DSC has an important role to play in public and private cloud deployments Apply DSC in the cloud with Microsoft Azu
r
e or Amazon Web Services or Google Cloud Platform Who This Book Is For IT administrators, developers and DevOps engineers working in Windows-based data center environments. With a little prior PowerShell scripting experience, this book can be used as an i
n
-depth reference to creating, customizing, and extending DSC in Windows. IT administrators with limited scripting experience will also find this book a useful overview of what DSC offers and how to use DSC resources to automate configuration management an
d
 deployment","edition":"Second edition","ISBN":"978-1-4842-3483-9","language":"eng","number-of-pages":"1","publisher":"Apress","publisher-place":"Place of publication not identified","source":"K10plus ISBN","title":"Pro PowerShell Desired State Configurat
ion: an in-depth guide to Windows PowerShell DSC","title-short":"Pro PowerShell Desired State Configuration","author":[\{"family":"Chaganti","given":"Ravikanth"\}],"issued":\{"date-parts":[["2018"]]\}\}\}
