\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid350903\charrsid3422972 
In the current system architecture, fixed passwords are used and injected at runtime through run_BuildMain.ps1. PSDscAllowPlainTextPassword = true is set to true in the AllNodes.psd1 file. This allows the plain text to be used }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12724054\charrsid3422972 
as a password instead of encrypted text. This setup works fine for a lab environment. But in a production environment, these expose the system vulnerability and make it easily breachable. Therefore, PSDscAllowPlainTextPassword = false is set to false, 
and certificate-encrypted MOF files are used to enhance the security. In a production environment, credentials will be used from Azure Key Vault at pipeline execution time}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14038560\charrsid3422972  }
