\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14681043\charrsid3422972 The PSDesiredStateConfiguration
 is version 2.0.8 on the virtual machine, but the instructor-required version is 2.0.7. This mismatch in the configuration causes the failure of the in one of the Pester preflight tests. This failure is caused of version mismatch instead of the issue in }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3370356\charrsid3422972 the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14681043\charrsid3422972 configuration, script, or design.}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid535152\charrsid3422972 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid14681043\charrsid3422972 
In automation, the tools version mismatch can cause errors during the automation and unexpected behavior, warnings, or test failures. In the case of BramBuzz, even though one test case fails due to a version mismatch, th
e DSC configuration is still successfully applied, and all the functionality works as intended, as evidenced by files in the Evidence folder.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1336498\charrsid3422972 In the current implementation of the GPO Script resources, it only checks for the GPO existence as 
discussed above, but in production-level enterprise systems, GPO values are checked if they are correctly configured in the registry, or links are correctly configured. Additionally, production implementation usually involves comparing the GPO values agai
nst good backup using Get-GPOReport and XML.
